 The Lagos State Judicial Panel has summoned the Inspector-General of Police (IGP), Mohammad Adamu over a case involving one Adewale Adewuyi, a petitioner who is on a stretcher.
Debo Adeleke, the petitioner’s lawyer, alleged that the police have refused to release 26 acres of farmland seized from the petitioner since 2013.
